S0.description:
⬇⬇⬇ STREAM SCHEDULE, LINKS, FAQs, ONLINE STORE and MORE HERE ⬇⬇⬇

Hello, 🙂 do you want to be more productive? Let's do it together! 💪 My name is Enrico, and the idea is simple: we are to do Study With Me Content for hours! 60 or 90 Minutes Style! With Rain sounds, conversations during breaks, and in real-time! I am a Harvard University alumnus (I graduated with a Master's Degree there), and  I will take you with me on my day (live!) Whether you study, work, or just want to be productive, this is the place for you! You guys are my Study Family ❤️, and we are here to support and motivate each other! Let's do this ✨💪

🌟 Buy My Digital Product for Better Productivity and Organization: https://enricovincente.gumroad.com/l/the3Cframework  
This is the 3C Framework - How to Organize your work and studies to achieve the Best Results!

═════

✦ CONTENTS OF THE DESCRIPTION BOX ✦ 

1 ● 📆 Schedule of the Live streams
2 ● 🤔 FAQs / Frequently Asked Questions
3 ● 💝 Online Store, Merch & Supporting the channel.
4 ● 📲 Social Media links
5 ● 👨‍🎓 How I Study & Work

═════

1 ● 📆 Schedule of the Live streams 

Stream Schedule: http://tinyurl.com/StreamScheduleEnrico
I am currently streaming "study with me" content every single day. I am  to work or study for 8-12 hours every day. I might do shorter streams sometimes. Take care of your health, guys, but with that being said, I am CHALLENGING myself and you, too! Do you  accept this challenge? Can you study or be productive every single day?  There is only one way to find out!

═════

2 ● 🤔 FAQs / Frequently Asked Questions

1. Why are you able to study 12 hours every day? How can I do it as well? 
Short answer. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Bm2MOzDc0JE  
Complete answer: https://youtu.be/SKdORiujdEI?si=RV34NVVUSy-HbRl5

2. How can you stay focused while studying for long hours? How can I do it too? Here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=N3bDBCgepsc :)

3. What do you listen to with your headphones? What music do you like?
I usually listen to the rain sound during the study with me live; the same sound you can hear from this live stream. Other times I listen to some study music. Here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jtFjwUj8_b4

4. How old are you? How tall are you? I was born on the 6th of January 1995. I am 1m and 83cm, 6 feet.

5. Where are you from? Do you study at Harvard? Did you graduate?
I'm from Italy, and I live in a city close to Venice. I studied at Harvard University and graduated there in 2024. Here is the graduation vlog: https://www.youtube.com/shorts/TVo2Ouqf0BU
Here is a video of me studying at Harvard: https://youtu.be/73_bJtalLa4?si=q-_o_RcMFFIqvlJT

6. What are you studying currently? Are you pursuing a degree?
I am currently studying animation and video production. I am not pursuing a degree. I am working on and learning this subject I am very passionate about: Animation.

7. What key Study Tips should I know? 
You MUST know these tips: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wsSAouA_O4M

8. How much time does Enrico sleep?
I average 7-8 hours. 

MORE FAQs: https://enricovincente.neocities.org/website/resources

═════

3 ● 💝 Online Store, Merch & Supporting the channel.

PATREON: https://www.patreon.com/enricovincente?fan_landing=true

SHOP: https://enricovincente.neocities.org/website/store 

FOR DONATIONS: https://paypal.me/MyNameIsEnrico?locale.x=it_IT

═════


4 ● 📲 Social Media Links

Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/enricovincente/ 

Discord: https://discord.gg/enricostudyfamily

Twitter: https://twitter.com/enricovincente

Animation Channel: https://www.youtube.com/@enricoanimated

═════

5 ● 👨‍🎓 How I Study & Work

My study session is a 60-minute or 90-minute Pomodoro Timer. Then, there will be a break of 10 minutes (or 9 or 15). During the live study with me, I repeat this for 8-14 hours. This is a double Pomodoro timer (60\10 or 60\9). The Pomodoro technique is very powerful. Breaks are essential to keep the efficiency of your study high. Always take them! I have a timer for all these scenarios. 
I alway study with Discipline ( https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2uhMr4eAhQY&t=0s ) and Self-Motivation. ( https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HliXs02QPR4&t=0s )

✔️ 학습시간 시작과 끝에는 학교종이 울려요.
✔️ 채팅은 쉬는시간에 봐요.

S5.description:
📩open me:

Hi!
Welcome to another Study with me
Thanks for joining
_________________________

I hope this study video helps you avoid using social media while you study. You will find a quiet and cosy study room ambience in this video when studying at your home. Hopefully, this would get you motivated more for studying. You might hear the rain, birds, typing sounds and the flipping of pages (and cars too, unfortunately) from time to time, and I hope that helps you know that I'm there studying with you!

🔥Key to success - """"BE CONSISTENT""""🔥

___________________________

What are you studying and where are you joining from? I also wonder what type of videos you like, study at the library or study at home? Your opinions are quite important to me; and, if you let me know what type of videos you like to watch, I would be happy. 
_____________________________

✧･ﾟ at the beginning of the study sessions, make sure to:
- turn off anything you're not going to be using to study
- have your materials ready to go
- have drinks/food ready so you don't have to get up to go get necessities
- have a clear idea of what you want to accomplish during the session (i.e., choose a task from your to-do list)


✧･ﾟ during the breaks:
- stop working as soon as the timer hits, even if you're mid-sentence
- make sure to get up, do some simple stretches
- refill anything that needs to get refilled
- talk to friends/update family

✧･ﾟ at the end of this video:
if you want to continue studying, give yourself a longer break and you can the next session video!

you're set to go! ♡
_____________________________
💡Please adjust the volume for each of the background music that comes out.
The ASMR that comes out with 💡 is the sound of burning wood and Rain. 
_____________________________

We have a Chat bot- 🤖
Commands for chat bot- 

!hi - when you join in👋
!start - to start studying
!top - Top Points
!points -  to know your points💯
!complete - when done with the goal

Chat rules:
- Being nice and respectful is mandatory!
- Spamming, harassment, trolling, bullying, repeating and all capital messages are definitely prohibited!
- Please feel encouraged to write in English so no one would feel excluded in the chat :)
- Please check YouTube's Community Guidelines
_____________________________

To those who are starting :
In order to study or do anything for long periods of time you need a strong purpose and you must be willing to endure challenges. If I can do this, think about what you can accomplish. If you're starting out, start from low intervals(10-30 minutes) and gradually increase once you feel you're comfortable. If you feel like quitting, visualize your goals and evaluate your purpose. Learn to accept challenges in your life to become uncommon.

S18.description:
Hello Everyone✨

This is Study Buddy Livestream ..Why U need this ...Read Below !! 

✅Claim of the Channel : 1 WEEK consistently Study With Me = Your Sitting Habit will SkyRocket🚀 

🙋🏻‍♂️Study with me - NEET, JEE, UPSC, CA, GATE, CLAT, HSC, SSC, JAMIA, CS, NDA, RBI and all other Exams 

✅WHY Study With Me✨ 

👉Many of Students around the globe faces challenges of Procrastination, Low Self motivation and not being able to stick to a routine, Non-interest when studying alone 
👉This is where LIVE Study streams help 
👉When u see someone else studying and knowing that there r others joining in on the same platform and toiling hard for their tasks, u also get the motivation to join in and stick around 
👉Just the fact that u r not there alone, sends a signal to ur brain to keep up the focus. Increased Productivity, motivation, confidence and good marks r just a by product.

Why am I streaming??
For me the best way to avoid procatination, avoid taking long breaks... is the stream where I follow each and every session honestly. Even if u all will follow me ... I bet after a month you will see improvement in ur sitting habits.

Why I am studying in dark?
In real I am getting sufficient light, its just the setting of my webcam due to which its's looking too dark.

About me : I am currently preparing for NEET UG (partial dropper)
